name: Pensacola Parks & Recreation After School Programs @ Cobb Resource Center
introduction: Pensacola Parks & Recreation After School programs provide educational and recreational enrichment opportunities through exciting experiences and exploration. Our After School programs offer activities which encourage children to be healthier and happier through active play, fitness and sports, dance and drama instruction, computer exploration and S.T.E.A.M. activities. Our program also includes homework-tutoring and a nutritious afternoon snack.
schools_served: Global Learning Academy; Jacqueline Harris Preparatory Academy; N. B. Cook Elementary School

name: All Kids Academy - School Age Program
introduction: All Kids Academy provides transportation to and from the local elementary schools in our area. Before and After School Program allows children to balance learning and fun through a variety of experiences. From homework help to fun physical activities, our program is designed so that everyone goes home happy.

name: Da Vinci Preschool Academy - After School
introduction: The foundation of every person is shaped during the preschool years. The desire to learn, the social skills, creativity, problem solving, auto control, self esteem... are all developed on these important years. Da Vinci Preschool Academy is dedicated to give your child the best opportunity of success for this challenging XXI Century. Da Vinci offers the following programs: Infant & Toddler, Preschool, VPK Program, After School.

name: Codeteachers Afterschool Program @ Apopka Elementary School
introduction: Codeteachers is proud to partner with Orange County Public Schools to bring our fun and innovative program to your kids and teens. Your child will learn storyline development, character creation, coding, design, emerging technology and how to run their own game studio! Kids will start by learning the fundamentals of coding and design by making games and will learn to create a virtual world. Our program is designed to meet the national standards in STEM: Science (NSES), technology, engineering (NGSS) & Math (CCMS), and it focuses on teaching kids confidence, leadership and using imagination to bring creations to life. There is a Showcase in May where you can see their games, projects and designs in action and play their creations!

name: Girls On The Run Northeast Florida @ Garden City Elementary
introduction: Northeast Florida is an Independent Council of Girls on the Run International, which has a network of 200+ locations across the United States and Canada. Girls on the Run® is a 501(c)3 non-profit organization dedicated to creating a world where every girl knows and activates her limitless potential and is free to boldly pursue her dreams. Over a period of 10 weeks, girls in the 3rd through 5th grade participate in an after-school program like no other. Designed to allow every girl to recognize her inner strength, the Girls on the Run curriculum inspires girls to define their lives on their own terms. Throughout the season, the girls make new friends, build their confidence and celebrate all that makes them unique. The Girls on the Run lessons encourage positive emotional, social, mental and physical development.  Participants explore and discuss their own beliefs around experiences and challenges girls face at this age.  They also develop important strategies and skills to help them navigate life experiences. We start with helping the girls get a better understanding of who they are and what’s important to them.  Then, we look at the importance of team work and healthy relationships.  And, finally, the girls explore how they can positively connect with and shape the world. Physical activity is woven into our program to inspire an appreciation of fitness and to build habits that lead to a lifetime of health.  At the end of each three month session, the girls participate in a Girls on the Run 5k event.  This celebratory, non-competitive event is the culminating experience of the curriculum.  Completing the 5k gives the girls a tangible understanding of the confidence that comes through accomplishment as well as a framework for setting and achieving life goals.  Crossing the finish line is a defining moment when the girls realize that even the seemingly impossible IS possible.

name: Girls On The Run Northeast Florida Heart & Sole @ Fletcher Middle School

name: Girls on the Run Orlando Heart & Sole @ Arbor Ridge Middle School
introduction: We are an Independent Council of Girls on the Run International, which has a network of 200+ locations across the United States and Canada. Girls on the Run® is a 501(c)3 non-profit organization dedicated to creating a world where every girl knows and activates her limitless potential and is free to boldly pursue her dreams. Heart & Sole is Girls on the Run’s new program for middle school girls! Heart & Sole creates a positive, structured space for middle school girls to learn about themselves, explore new ideas, cultivate empathy, strengthen connections and develop life skills that will help them as they move through adolescence and beyond. The Heart & Sole curriculum is rich with themes girls can relate to, addressing the whole girl - body, brain, heart, spirit and social connection - and building important life skills such as team building, developing a support system, boundary setting, decision making, asking for and providing help and more. This 10-week program is accessible to all girls regardless of athletic ability or fitness level and considers the range of ages and varied experiences of middle schoolers. Physical activity includes strength and conditioning appropriate for this age group. The season culminates with the Girls on the Run 5k, which is the celebratory event that underscores the confidence, competence, connection, character and caring they’ve been developing in the program and gives them a tangible sense of goal setting and achievement.

name: Girls on the Run of Collier County @ Avalon Elementary
introduction: We are an Independent Council of Girls on the Run International, which has a network of 200+ locations across the United States and Canada. Girls on the Run® is a 501(c)3 non-profit organization dedicated to creating a world where every girl knows and activates her limitless potential and is free to boldly pursue her dreams. Meeting twice a week in small teams of 8-15 girls, we teach life skills through dynamic, conversation-based lessons and running games. The 24-lesson curriculum is taught by certified Girls on the Run coaches and includes three parts: understanding ourselves, valuing relationships and teamwork and understanding how we connect with and shape the world at large. Running is used to inspire and motivate girls, encourage lifelong health and fitness, and build confidence through accomplishment. At each season's conclusion, the girls and their running buddies, complete a 5k running event. Completing a 5k gives the girls a tangible sense of achievement as well as a framework for setting and achieving life goals. The result - making the seemingly impossible, possible and teaching girls that they can.

name: Girls on the Run of the Treasure Coast Heart & Sole @ Gifford Middle School
introduction: Heart & Sole is the middle school program geared for 6th-8th graders. The principal philosophy behind both programs is the same, yet the depth of processing varies in order to be age appropriate. The Girls on Track middle school curriculum allows for more mature processing around certain topics including eating disorders, internet safety, cyber bullying and tobacco and alcohol use. Today's middle-school girls face many challenges and obstacles that can affect their emotional and physical well-being. The Girls on Track curriculum is designed to address these challenges by empowering them to make thoughtful and healthy decisions. Like Girls on the Run, the Girls on Track curriculum is delivered over the course of 10 to 12 weeks and addresses the societal, mental and emotional challenges particular to their age. Like the Girls on the Run curricula, we begin by encouraging the girls to examine and better understand who they are and what's important to them. Once they have a deeper awareness of their individual values, we look at the role of teams and healthy relationships. Lastly, the girls explore how they can positively connect with and shape the world. The curriculum allows for more mature processing around certain topics including eating disorders, internet safety, relationships, cyber-bullying and tobacco and alcohol use. The girls discuss these subjects on an in-depth level and use their personal experiences to shape thought-provoking discussion. The Girls on Track curriculum provides girls with the skills to shut out the noise of the external world that is attempting to limit who she is and to instead listen to her individual truth – the one that will lead her toward an enriching and contented life. Running is also incorporated into the curriculum. We use physical activity to inspire and motivate girls throughout the program, to encourage lifelong health and fitness, and most importantly, to build confidence through accomplishment. At the end of each season, the girls and their running buddies complete a 5k running event which gives the girls a tangible sense of achievement as well as a framework for setting and achieving life goals. This culminating celebratory 5k event is a transformative moment when the girls realize that even the seemingly impossible IS possible.

name: Girls on the Run of the Treasure Coast @ Citrus Elementary
introduction: Girls on the Run is for 3rd-5th graders, helping them prepare for a lifetime of self-respect and healthy living using interactive and creative running activities, games and discussion. Over a period of 12 weeks, girls in the 3rd through 5th grade participate in an after-school program like no other. Designed to allow every girl to recognize her inner strength, the Girls on the Run curriculum inspires girls to define their lives on their own terms. Throughout the season, the girls make new friends, build their confidence and celebrate all that makes them unique. The Girls on the Run lessons encourage positive emotional, social, mental and physical development.  Participants explore and discuss their own beliefs around experiences and challenges girls face at this age.  They also develop important strategies and skills to help them navigate life experiences. We start with helping the girls get a better understanding of who they are and what’s important to them.  Then, we look at the importance of team work and healthy relationships.  And, finally, the girls explore how they can positively connect with and shape the world. Physical activity is woven into our program to inspire an appreciation of fitness and to build habits that lead to a lifetime of health.  At the end of each three month session, the girls participate in a Girls on the Run 5k event.  This celebratory, non-competitive event is the culminating experience of the curriculum.  Completing the 5k gives the girls a tangible understanding of the confidence that comes through accomplishment as well as a framework for setting and achieving life goals.  Crossing the finish line is a defining moment when the girls realize that even the seemingly impossible IS possible.

name: Girls on the Run Volusia County @ Debary Elementary
introduction: Girls on the Run® is a life-changing program for third- to eighth-grade girls. Our mission is to inspire girls to be joyful, healthy and confident using a fun, experience-based curriculum which creatively integrates running. We use the power of running to provide girls with the tools to: Celebrate their bodies; Honor their voices; Recognize their gifts, and Activate their personal power. Girls on the Run of Volusia County started in 2005 and is an affiliate council of Girls on the Run International. Founded in 1996 by Molly Barker - a visionary, Ironman triathlete, Girls on the Run has about 208 locations across the U.S. & Canada, with new locations added each year. Girls on the Run® combines training for a 5k (3.1 miles) event with healthy living education. We use exercise, positive reinforcement, and encouraging role models to help girls discover the confidence they need in the critical pre-teen years and beyond.
pricing: Program Registration Fee: $100.00

We use the power of running to provide girls with the tools to: Celebrate their bodies; Honor their voices; Recognize their gifts, and Activate their personal power. Girls on the Run of Volusia County started in 2005 and is an affiliate council of Girls on the Run International. Founded in 1996 by Molly Barker - a visionary, Ironman triathlete, Girls on the Run has about 208 locations across the U.S. & Canada, with new locations added each year. Girls on the Run® combines training for a 5k (3.1 miles) event with healthy living education. We use exercise, positive reinforcement, and encouraging role models to help girls discover the confidence they need in the critical pre-teen years and beyond.

name: Girls On The Run of Alachua County @ Archer Elementary
introduction: We are an Independent Council of Girls on the Run International, which has a network of 200+ locations across the United States and Canada. Girls on the Run® is a 501(c)3 non-profit organization dedicated to creating a world where every girl knows and activates her limitless potential and is free to boldly pursue her dreams. Over a period of 12 weeks, girls in the 3rd through 5th grade participate in an after-school program like no other. Designed to allow every girl to recognize her inner strength, the Girls on the Run curriculum inspires girls to define their lives on their own terms. Throughout the season, the girls make new friends, build their confidence and celebrate all that makes them unique. The Girls on the Run lessons encourage positive emotional, social, mental and physical development. Participants explore and discuss their own beliefs around experiences and challenges girls face at this age. They also develop important strategies and skills to help them navigate life experiences. We start with helping the girls get a better understanding of who they are and what’s important to them. Then, we look at the importance of team work and healthy relationships. And, finally, the girls explore how they can positively connect with and shape the world. Physical activity is woven into our program to inspire an appreciation of fitness and to build habits that lead to a lifetime of health. At the end of each three month session, the girls participate in a Girls on the Run 5k event. This celebratory, non-competitive event is the culminating experience of the curriculum. Completing the 5k gives the girls a tangible understanding of the confidence that comes through accomplishment as well as a framework for setting and achieving life goals. Crossing the finish line is a defining moment when the girls realize that even the seemingly impossible IS possible.

name: Girls On The Run of Alachua County Heart & Sole @ Ft. Clarke Middle
introduction: We are an Independent Council of Girls on the Run International, which has a network of 200+ locations across the United States and Canada. Girls on the Run® is a 501(c)3 non-profit organization dedicated to creating a world where every girl knows and activates her limitless potential and is free to boldly pursue her dreams. At Girls on the Run, we believe that adolescents bring a lot to the table. We also know that girls at this age often sort through conflicting messages about their worth, their abilities and their value. Our middle school programs help girls develop the skills to tune into their own truths and to unleash their power to live confidently and joyfully. Heart & Sole is Girls on the Run’s new program for middle school girls! Heart & Sole creates a positive, structured space for middle school girls to learn about themselves, explore new ideas, cultivate empathy, strengthen connections and develop life skills that will help them as they move through adolescence and beyond. The Heart & Sole curriculum is rich with themes girls can relate to, addressing the whole girl—body, brain, heart, spirit and social connection - and building important life skills such as team building, developing a support system, boundary setting, decision making, asking for and providing help, and more. This 10-week program is accessible to all girls regardless of athletic ability or fitness level and considers the range of ages and varied experiences of middle schoolers. Physical activity includes strength and conditioning appropriate for this age group. The season culminates with the Girls on the Run 5k, which is the celebratory event that underscores the confidence, competence, connection, character and caring they’ve been developing in the program and gives them a tangible sense of goal setting and achievement.

name: Girls on the Run Space Coast @ Boys and Girls Club - Central
introduction: GOTR Space Coast is an Independent Council of Girls on the Run International, which has a network of 200+ locations across the United States and Canada. Girls on the Run® is a 501(c)3 non-profit organization dedicated to creating a world where every girl knows and activates her limitless potential and is free to boldly pursue her dreams. Meeting twice a week in small teams of 8-15 girls, we teach life skills through dynamic, conversation-based lessons and running games. The 20-lesson curriculum is taught by certified Girls on the Run coaches and includes three parts: understanding ourselves, valuing relationships and teamwork and understanding how we connect with and shape the world at large. Running is used to inspire and motivate girls, encourage lifelong health and fitness, and build confidence through accomplishment. At each season's conclusion, the girls and their running buddies complete a 5k running event. Completing a 5k gives the girls a tangible sense of achievement as well as a framework for setting and achieving life goals. The result—making the seemingly impossible, possible and teaching girls that they can.

name: Girls on the Run Greater Tampa Bay @ Academy of the Holy Names
introduction: Girls on the Run Greater Tampa Bay is an Affiliate Council of Girls on the Run International, which has a network of 200+ locations across the United States and Canada. Girls on the Run® is a 501(c)3 non-profit organization dedicated to creating a world where every girl knows and activates her limitless potential and is free to boldly pursue her dreams. Over the course of the ten-week program, girls in 3rd-5th grade develop essential skills to help them navigate their worlds and establish a lifetime appreciation for health and fitness. The program culminates with girls positively impacting their communities through a service project and being physically and emotionally prepared to complete a celebratory 5k event.

name: Girls Place Inc. After School Program
introduction: The Girls Place After School Program operates in conjunction with the Alachua County School Calendar.  We transport girls from many Alachua County schools to Girls Place for an afternoon of structured activities.  We provide a wide variety of activities based on the components of physical, emotional, spiritual, environmental, intellectual and social wellness.  This curriculum, with an emphasis on homework completion, allows Girls Place to provide a well rounded experience for the girls.  Girls will participate in arts and crafts and field trips, interacting with special guests, and much more. Girls ages 5-18 can participate in our after school program.  Girls are divided into groups based on the grade they are entering at the beginning of the school year: Kindergarten-1st Grade - Pink Group; 2nd-3rd Grade - Red Group; 4th-5th Grade - Yellow Group; 6th-7th Grade - Green Group; 8th-12th Grade - Blue Group. Each group has designated classroom space in addition to access to about 5 acres of green space and a gymnasium.
pricing: An active Girls Place Membership is required to participate in all programs. Individual Membership - $20/year, Family Membership (2+ Girls) - $40/year; After School: Elementary School (1st Child) - $52/Week, Elementary School (2nd Child) - $43/Week, Middle and High School - $32/Week, Late Pick-Up (after 6pm) - $1 for every 5 minutes you are late.
schools_served: Chiles Elementary; Cornerstone Academy; Glen Springs Elementary; Hidden Oak Elementary; Littlewood Elementary; Meadowbrook Elementary; Norton Elementary; One Room Schoolhouse; PK Yonge; Stephen Foster Elementary; Talbot Elementary; Terwilliger Elementary; Fort Clarke Middle School; Howard Bishop Middle School; Westwood Middle School

name: Palm Bay After School Program
introduction: Our After School Program is committed to your child’s success in school! Each day your child will have the opportunity to complete all of his/her homework assignments with the help of our caring after school program leaders. We will make sure that your child’s home work is done on time each day, so you don’t have to worry! Other after school programs can’t compare! We are not a daycare, county park, or babysitter. We are much better! From the moment you join our after school team, you and your child will feel welcome because our after school program students are like family! We focus on your child’s success in School, Sports, and life! Other after school programs “babysit” their kids, but we inspire our kids to be their BEST! We only hire the BEST coaches and they truly care about your child’s success! Our after school program and summer camp is operated by talented coaches who have years of experience and who have all passed a level 2 background checks! (The same background check required to be a School Teacher in Palm Bay, FL.)
additionalInfo: Daily A+ Homework Assistance; Martial Arts Classes; Dance Classes; Cheerleading and Tumbling Classes; Outdoor Sports; Arts and Crafts; Game Rooms; Character Development
schools_served: Columbia Elementary; Discovery Elementary; Jupiter Elementary; Turner Elementary; Meadowlane Elementary; Odyssey Charter; Pineapple Cove Classical Academy; Port Malabar Elementary; Christa Mcauliffe Elementary; Lockmar Elementary; Royal Palm Charter; Sunrise Elementary; Westside Elementary

name: Bennett Elementary After School Care from Sunshine
introduction: We currently provide nearly 5,000 students, in over THIRTY-FIVE Broward County elementary and middle schools, with before and/or after school programs this year. All of our programs operate under the policies and directives of the five year RFP contract retained with the Broward County School Board. Additionally, all programs meet and/or exceed the licensing requirements of the Division of Children and Family Services (HRS). After School Programs fees are based on a monthly payment schedule plus a registration fee. Sunshine also has many programs that are grant funded. These rates are based on the family’s income. Their purpose is to make aftercare accessible to families that may otherwise have a hard time affording it. Sunshine After School Programs include an individually wrapped snack and juice drink for each student. We follow a daily planned schedule of developmentally appropriate activities. These include student academic support for homework, reading enrichment, arts and crafts, music, dance, organized sports, outside play, and indoor games. Certified teachers are hired to work with students in our after school programs to facilitate many of these specialized student activities.

introduction: We currently provide nearly 5,000 students, in over THIRTY-FIVE Broward County elementary and middle schools, with before and/or after school programs this year. All of our programs operate under the policies and directives of the five year RFP contract retained with the Broward County School Board. Sunshine After School Programs include an individually wrapped snack and juice drink for each student. We follow a daily planned schedule of developmentally appropriate activities. These include student academic support for homework, reading enrichment, arts and crafts, music, dance, organized sports, outside play, and indoor games. Certified teachers are hired to work with students in our after school programs to facilitate many of these specialized student activities.

name: St. Ambrose Catholic School After School Care from Sunshine
introduction: We currently provide nearly 5,000 students, in over THIRTY-FIVE Broward County elementary and middle schools, with before and/or after school programs this year. All of our programs operate under the policies and directives of the five year RFP contract retained with the Broward County School Board. Additionally, all programs meet and/or exceed the licensing requirements of the Division of Children and Family Services (HRS). name: J University After School Program
introduction: We provide a safe, enriching, and fun after school experience for children in grades K-5, five days a week until 6 p.m. J University is supervised by full-time staff and is compliant with the Department of Children and Families policies and procedures.   At the JCC, children of all faiths are embraced.
additionalInfo: Snack; Fun Activities; Homework; Special Classes & Private Lessons
pricing: Registration Fee:  $125 for the first child,  $50 for each additional child; Monthly Tuition: 2 Days per week: $275 with transportation, $175 Jewish Academy students; 3 Days per week: $305 with transportation, $205 Jewish Academy students; 4 Days per week: $335 with transportation, $235 Jewish Academy students; 5 Days per week: $365 with transportation, $265 Jewish Academy students; Sibling Discount: Second Child 50% off, Third Child 75% off, Any Additional Children FREE.

name: Pahokee Youth Enrichment Academy @ Pahokee Elementary
introduction: The Youth Enrichment Academies (YEA) are licensed after school programs serving school-aged children aged 5 - 12 years old.  Children enjoy a wide variety of activities and programming that develop the assets in youth which lead to resilience and success.  Our family-centered Youth Enrichment Academy programs are open daily from 2pm to 6pm and all day for eight weeks of summer camp. The PYEA and the PPYEA programs have been serving the Glades community now for over ten years.

name: A+ Kids Learning Academy After School
introduction: A+ Kids Learning Academy is family-owned and operated and has been serving the needs of families in the Waterford Lakes area for more than ten years. We currently serve students ranging from 1 to 12 years old.

name: After School Kicks - After School Soccer Program
introduction: Soccer has been proven as a way to enhance and develop fitness, endurance, coordination, footwork, and physical technique. Our coaching staff has developed a program that will focus on the key aspects of soccer. This program provides each child with the necessary tools to excel and enjoy the game, while having fun learning. Our goal is to develop each child's individual skill, encourage team building, and teach the fundamentals of soccer! Children enjoy a snack and drink before taking field time to learn soccer, kickball, dodgeball, wiffle ball, and much more. Video games and board games can be enjoyed after participation in field time and with parent approval.  Don't let your child travel after school with no air conditioning, let us use our air-conditioned vans! Our fleet of vans minimizes the time your child is on the road, and maximizes the time they get to have fun while enhancing their skills. We provide free transportation services from over 15 Pinellas County Schools.
additionalInfo: Transportation; Snack & Drink; Soccer and other team games; Tutoring
pricing: Price: $89/week for 1st child; $79/week for 2nd child (Special Discount: 10% off when you pay for a month in full. Call for further discounts if you pay for the entire year in full)

name: Broadway Kids Studio After-School Program
introduction: Broadway Kids Studio’s After-School Program is one of the most popular and innovative in not just South Florida but the entire United States. The benefits of the program are numerous including students receiving the most well-rounded performing arts education available. Students that take part in our After-School Program receive a significant discount on our normal group class rate. The program has two options (one that includes transportation from select local schools or a drop off option for a lower rate). Regardless of drop-off or pick-up, everyone is entitled to up to 15 classes per week included with tuition. Students take part in classes from 3pm-6pm daily or 4pm-7pm for our older students. Included is a wide range of performing art classes in singing, acting, dancing and exposure to instruments. Siblings also receive an additional discount.

name: Kids and Company Bumby Afterschool Program
introduction: Our Afterschool Program provides an environment that is safe, comfortable, and has a lot of interest areas. The after-school environment includes a variety of indoor and outdoor space and is equipped with age appropriate materials and supplies for the number of children served. This program is available all year round, during school time, No school, most holidays and summer time. Our well trained staff promotes strategies to guide children in the development of communication, problem solving, self-help, and conflict resolution skills. Every day our children are given opportunities to participate in activities that teach them new concepts and skills that support their school day.Educationally supportive activities is homework assistance. Daily right after snack is homework time, reading/writing activities, hands on discovery experiences and math games. Program staff is available to assist children with homework-related tasks. Other related activities may include; read-a louds, buddy reading, books, story writing, creative dramatics, and journal keeping. Games that enhance children's problem solving skills, deductive reasoning skills, and math related skills. The most pleasant time in the day for an after school-age is outdoor activities. At our large fence playgrounds our after school-age feels freedom in a relaxed atmosphere. Children are encouraged to interact with one another in positive ways. Staff guide children toward positive and appropriate behavior and rules are consistently communicated positively and are posted visually to encourage children to regulate their own behavior. Kids Club is game room for the exclusive use of the school age children to have fun. Arcades, table games, props, music and much more. In addition by providing flexible scheduling and extended hours of care including Saturday, Kids & Company school-age program attempts to meet the needs of children and their families enrolled in our program.

additionalInfo: Homework/Computer assistance; Career Presentations; Monthly Birthday Celebrations; Group Talk; Nutritional Snacks; Reading circles; Cub Room (grades Kindergarten - 1st grade); Fitness Class; Arts and Crafts; Outdoor Play

name: Orlando After-School All-Stars @ Carver Middle School
introduction: Orlando After-School All-Stars provides comprehensive youth development programs that keep children safe and help them achieve in school and life. Orlando ASAS serves over 2,600 students and their families annually in our year round programs. All programs are school based and tailored to supplement and enhance the existing efforts of each specific school site. Orlando ASAS’s programming centers around the core components of academics, enrichment, athletics and service learning. The organization utilizes an innovative and diversified year round curriculum to engage youth so that they may develop the life-skills, maturity and confidence necessary to become responsible and productive citizens at home, school and in their community. Through generous support from the City of Orlando, Mayor Buddy Dyer and the City Council, Orlando ASAS continues to be the community leader in providing safe, free and comprehensive after-school and summer programming for Orlando’s middle school age youth.

name: Proletics Martial Arts & Fitness After School Program
introduction: Enroll your child in an enriching, fun afterschool program - that provides transportation. We pick your child up from school, and bring them to our facility for an afternoon full of martial art, fun & games and of course homework. Your child will learn first hand about responsibility, discipline, respect and confidence, while enjoying the camaraderie of fellow students. So while you are at work you can rest assured that your child is at a safe, fun and structured program to take care of you child we are here to make that happen for you. We look forward to training your bundle of joy.

name: Minds In Motion LLC - After School S.T.E.M. Program
introduction: Our goal is to provide your child with a quality after school program that combines enrichment through S.T.E.M. concepts and hands-on exploration in a fun, safe environment!
pricing: Price: $70.00 / week; $60.00 material / lab fee due at enrollment; Discount available for additional siblings

name: Easterseals South Florida After School Program
introduction: Easterseals South Florida provides FREE year-round (afterschool and summer) services, offering activities for elementary and middle school children (6-12 years old). The program includes literacy and homework support, physical fitness, social skills and a variety of enrichment activities involving music, art, dance and a unique French Heritage Language Program which is offered by the Haitian Cultural Art Alliance. After school services will be available for 157 elementary and middle school slots for 130 typically-developing children and 27 children with disabilities.  Summer camp services will be available for 96 elementary and middle school slots for 60 typically-developing children and 36 children with disabilities residing in the city of Miami, Little Haiti and surrounding neighborhoods. During the school year, snacks are provided free of charge thru Department of Health Afterschool Snacks Program. Summer lunches and snacks are provided  free of charge by The Village South.

name: Easterseals South Florida After School Program @ Little Haiti Cultural Center
introduction: Easterseals South Florida provides FREE year-round (afterschool and summer) services, offering activities for elementary and middle school children (6-12 years old). The program includes literacy and homework support, physical fitness, social skills and a variety of enrichment activities involving music, art, dance and a unique French Heritage Language Program which is offered by the Haitian Cultural Art Alliance. After school services will be available for 157 elementary and middle school slots for 130 typically-developing children and 27 children with disabilities.  Summer camp services will be available for 96 elementary and middle school slots for 60 typically-developing children and 36 children with disabilities residing in the city of Miami, Little Haiti and surrounding neighborhoods. During the school year, snacks are provided free of charge thru Department of Health Afterschool Snacks Program. Summer lunches and snacks are provided  free of charge by The Village South.

name: Orlando Science Center Afterschool
introduction: Orlando Science Center Afterschool is an immersive afterschool program providing Central Florida students in grades K-5 the opportunity to build 21st Century skills through enriching, hands-on STEM activities. Each quarter, the program will provide an interdisciplinary approach to various STEM topics in an afterschool environment that fosters skill development over time while encouraging existing interests and passions. Through engagement in project-based activities, students will be provided with opportunities for self-direction and access to various disciplines such as arts, social studies, and more. This program runs Monday – Friday.

name: Authentic Martial Arts of Largo After School Program
introduction: Research has shown that kids who stay physically fit can concentrate longer. Our tutoring program is included in our after school program free of charge. Our busy parents know they have an academic partner to help make sure their children don’t slip behind in school. Our program can even help them move ahead in their current grade, or advance their learning to the next grade level. Each child takes an academic assessment,  and then an Individual Learning Plan is created. This is not a “one size fits all” approach. Our academic tutoring program keeps our “Karate Kids” academically sharp and mentally prepared year round. And it’s fun too!

name: ASF After School Program For Kids
hoursopen: After School Schedule: 2:00pm - 6:30pm; Teacher Planning, Early Release, Day Camp and Holiday Day Schedule: 7:30am - 6:00pm
introduction: ASF After School Program For Kids is an exclusive educational and cultural program available to children ages 5-15 years old. We provide the unique opportunity for kids to discover and experience Japanese culture from Chief Instructor Stephanie Yap Sensei, 6th dan, who has lived in Japan for numerous years and has been teaching at Aikido of South Florida since she founded the school over 25 years ago. Our After School Program For Kids will introduce your child to several disciplines in a fun environment: training of the wonderful non-violent martial art Aikido, the simplicity of movement and the breath in yoga and meditation! We ensure your child will be well supervised while they are in our hands.

name: Space Coast Early Intervention Center After School Program
introduction: The  After-School Program is designed to provide stimulating interactive learning activities for elementary age children with disabilities and their typically developing siblings and peers in a safe after school setting. The program runs from 2:00 pm to 6:00 pm. The inclusive After-School program goals are to offer children with mental, physical and social delays and their typical peers opportunities to engage in meaningful creative learning activities in a structured non-stressful environment. Weekly, children from local elementary schools will participate in a variety of activities in small groups with adult leaders. Every child will be checked in at arrival and offered snack and down time until arrival of all participants. Children with disabilities are eligible for transportation to SCEIC’s facility by the Brevard Public School Bus System if they are in the 2 mile radius feeder zone of SCEIC. Coordination for special needs transportation is set up between the parent and their elementary school’s transportation coordinator.

name: CCFC YouthPride After School Program @ CCFC
introduction: CCFC’s commitment to building strong communities starts with our children. In 1992 after Hurricane Andrew, our agency helped support and entertain children in Florida City/Homestead who with their parents had become homeless. Believing that no investment is more important than one which helps children succeed in school, CCFC offers free, tutorial-based after school and summer camp to 200 unduplicated children ages 5-15 from PK-8th grade each year.  Since 2007, our organization has been designated a 21st Century Community Learning Center by the Florida Dept. of Education. With funding from the U.S. Dept. of Education, United Way of Miami-Dade and Volunteer Florida, which funds 14 half-time AmeriCorps members to mentor our children, CCFC supports children who attend low-performing schools in our area and whose parents, have often had interrupted education opportunities. Many of our parents have limited English literacy which affects their ability to assist their children with homework and extra activities. Often working two jobs & enduring financial hardships,  parents cannot afford full-time summer camp to support their children’s regular school learning, nor  afford after school services to keep their children on track with all their daily assignments. Without YouthPride, many of our community’s children would likely be home alone or watched by siblings who are not equipped to help with homework or special projects.

name: FAU/Pine Jog Afterschool Program
hoursopen: Program Full Time Hours: 2:05pm - 6:05pm; Program Part Time Hours: 2:05pm - 4:05pm; Early Release Days: 11:25am - 6:05pm
introduction: Our mission is to provide a quality afterschool program that enriches and enhances the lives of the students and parents that attend our program. We commit ourselves to teach diversity and respect so that our youth can become productive environmental citizens. The philosophy of the FAU/Pine Jog Afterschool Program is to provide a quality afterschool program for the students that attend Pine Jog Elementary School. Our goal is to meet the fundamental needs for growth and development for all children attending our program by providing a safe and healthy environment. It is important that children be given the best possible opportunities to grow into healthy, well-adjusted youth. Our goal is to introduce new and exciting activities such as drumming, storytelling, nature hikes, dance troops, etc. We will continue to introduce more healthy snacks choices into our program. Students will have the opportunity to choose what they cook once a month.
additionalInfo: Homework; Arts & Craft; SPARKS (Sports Play & Active Recreation for Kids); Environmental Literacy; Gardening; STEM (Science, Technology, Engineering and Mathematics); Music and Dance; Cooking; Inside Games; Computer Lab

name: GASP
introduction: Founded in the early 2000s by Wayne Gabb, an enrichment math teacher at Talbot Elementary, Mr. Gabb's After School Program (GASP) was developed on the principal that learning can be fun for teachers and kids. Although Mr. Gabb retired from teaching in 2014, his dedication to education lives on through GASP, where life skills and good study habits are a focus. In Mr. Gabb's stead, Shelby Stocker has taken over the program after 5 years working and learning from the founder, as well as the children themselves. A recent University of Florida graduate, Shelby hopes to employ skills learned throughout her collegiate studies to take the program above and beyond it's original grandeur. GASP is committed to employing staffers who model character and integrity. They assist with everything from tying shoes, to conflict resolution, to working through those tough math problems. The staffers are the heart and soul of this program. During the academic year, the GASP schedule includes half an hour of dedicated homework time. Additionally, at your request, we can also ensure your child's homework is complete - and even checked by a staff member - before you pick them up. Think academics end with the school year? Not at GASP. Summer camp mornings are dedicated to academic instruction and review provided by certified elementary school teachers. GASP's goal is to help keep those young minds fresh and support their success in the coming year. And our BIGGEST GASP goal: to we partner with parents to ensure their children receive the academic, life, and social support they need to thrive!  GASP Great for kids. Perfect for parents.
additionalInfo: Arts & Crafts; Video Games & Screen Time; Playground; On The Court; Rainy Day Activities: Bingo, Board games, Wii 'Just Dance', Movies, Arts & Crafts, GASP Library

name: TLC Kid - After School Program
introduction: After school program is currently offered at Fort Lauderdale Learning Center. Outstanding afterschool programs for elementary and secondary school children.  Our programs include certified teachers and tutors that supervise homework, computer and study time. Unique to our programs are our “arts” centers that provide education, recreation and cultivation of our childrens talents: music, chorus, kids orchestra, martial arts, culinary arts, visual and creative arts, drama, arts & crafts, painting and fun fitness through yoga classes, hip hop and kick boxing.

name: Diamond Minds Transformational Leadership Academy After-School
introduction: Our after-school program offers a variety of services, including homework completion, test preparation, individualized tutoring (as needed), social skills development, and opportunities to improve physical fitness. Completion of homework is one of our top priorities therefore an 30 minutes to an hour of each day is dedicated to homework. Although this is of extreme importance to us there are some occasions in which all of the homework can not be completed. Subsequently, parents must provide assistance at home to ensure it is completed. If students are unable to complete their homework during the allotted time this information will be communicated to parents. At least one hour each day will be dedicated to promoting reading and literacy. This will be done through teacher instruction and in various creative ways. Several months of each year are devoted to SAT and other test preparation, with one goal being to improve students’ test taking skills. Students will be responsible for developing a newsletter for families, teachers, and The Children’s Trust. We will also utilize a variety of software to enhance student literacy and math skills. There are certified teachers on staff who specialize in Science, Humanities, Computer Technology, Literacy, and Mathematics. One-on-one and small group tutoring is offered to students in need of intensive intervention.
additionalInfo: Homework support; Dance; Art; Music Instruction; Healthy Snack Options

name: PAL of St. Petersburg - After School Program
introduction: The afterschool program offers a safe and secure environment for your children while you work. It consists of a healthy snack, structured homework time, free play, sports & fitness, character education sessions, music, art and computer time. After school operates five days per week, from 2 pm - 6 pm, throughout the school year. Students are transported from local schools to our facility, where they can choose from a variety of enrichment activities. Each day includes dedicated homework time, as well as access to our computer lab. Creativity is encouraged through music, art projects, and free play. Outdoor activities and nature exploration give students a chance to play outside in a safe environment. PAL offers all of these activities, including snack and school transport, for a reasonable week fee.
pricing: After school fees - $48 weekly and includes snack and transportation from local schools.

Each day your child will have the opportunity to complete all of his/her homework assignments with the help of our caring after school program leaders. Our after school program and summer camp is operated by talented coaches who have years of experience and who have all passed a level 2 background checks! name: American TKA Kids After School Martial Arts Program
introduction: Our goal with the “TKA Kids After School Martial Arts Program” is to provide quality care for the children in a safe environment utilizing appropriate martial arts activities to meet individual needs. We build character through Martial Arts Training. A true Martial Artist lives a life of Honor through their actions, they are leaders and earn respect through what they say and do each and every day. This is what we create and we take great pride in our proven track record.  After 20+ years in the same location, as of September 1st, 2016 we are moving 1 mile West to a new location; 10376 State Rd 84, Davie Fl 33324. American TKA Martial Arts provides an After School Martial Arts program that enhances the lives of children. Physically we develop their balance, strength, coordination, and fitness that helps them grow to be strong & confident in their abilities. Mentally we plant in them fundamental values of respect, discipline, positive attitude, and persistence that will help them lead happy and fulfilling lives. Emotionally we give them self confidence, self esteem, and a sense of self worth to help them make sound, positive decisions wherever they may go or wherever they may be. This is the critical aspect in teaching children these fundamental skills which prevents them from becoming the victim of bullying. American TKA owner, Master Ginarte speaks to school teachers on a weekly basis, attends conferences & reviews each students reports cards quarterly to monitor students progression. Master Ginarte created our “Triangle Principle” which focuses on all 3 points converging together for the child’s success, (Home, School & Martial Arts). This is used in every aspect of our program. Our program includes 7 forms of Martial Arts, (Tae Kwon Do, MMA, Muay Thai, Brazilian Jiu Jitsu, Boxing, Capoeira & Parkour. We also conduct weekly boot-camp workouts at local parks & teach extensive weapons programs. We have competition teams & are heavily involved in community projects as a basis of giving back. No other Martial Arts Schools offer the diverse programs we do and we take pride in our accomplishments and reputation. American TKA After School Martial Arts Program is a priority for our school. Personal safety, focus, character development, & improved academics are only some of the benefits of this program;  Studies  have found that martial arts training has a direct correlation with improvement of children’s school grades. Our After School Martial Arts Program is perfect for moms and dads! It is a week-to-week, year round program that takes the place of daycare, extended care or babysitting. As an added convenience we offer full day programs on teacher workdays, school half days and most holidays. Students will enjoy fun days with diverse activities in addition to their martial arts training. We may visit local parks and area attractions or perhaps invite a guest speaker or performer. Of course our facilities offer plenty of opportunities for fun too. Maybe a kid’s movie, state of the art entertainment systems or an exciting day participating in Indoor Olympic Games. Whether students are enjoying a day of indoor soccer or watching an exciting movie, you can be sure your child will have a great time with the varied activities.

What draws most parents to our program are our in-house webcams that allows you to view your child at anytime  just by logging on to our website with your own secure password. While enrolled in our “Little Champions” program, your children will have the chance to interact with other positive minded children and they will be staying active and fit by receiving karate and martial arts instruction. name: Achievement Centers for Children and Families - Afterschool at Family Resource Center
introduction: The Afterschool Program is located in the Morton Downey Family Resource Center (FRC) on the main campus. We promote early and consistent success in school and provide continuity of care for children through the teen years. The After School Program is open from 2 p.m. to 7 p.m. Monday through Friday. Educational enrichment programs, daily homework assistance and special FCAT preparation are important components of our after-school program. We also offer a wide variety of clubs and activities for creative expression and skill building. Students may choose to participate in clubs and activities including music, drumline, dance, art, drama, ceramics, sewing club and basketball. The FRC features the James Lippingwell Computer Lab, a recording studio, a library, study rooms, art center, performing art stage, gym and multiple playground areas. Hot meals and snacks are provided daily at no additional charge. The After School Program serves students in grades K through 8th from 12 elementary schools. Direct school bus routes, with drop-off and pick-up, provides door-to-door service and guarantees children’s attendance.

introduction: The curriculum consists of academic support, cultural enrichment, recreational activities, and leadership programs.

name: Achievement Centers for Children and Families - Afterschool at Village Academy
introduction: The Afterschool Program has a heavy academic focus for these students who are at the highest risk for academic failure and school dropout. The Afterschool Program serves Village Academy students in grades K through 6th. It’s an “extension of the school day” from 2 p.m. until 7 p.m., Monday through Friday and is located in the Village Academy School. Guided coursework, homework assistance and additional FCAT preparation are provided. Students participate in a curriculum that emphasizes good moral character and making wise decisions. Clubs, activities and field trips offer cultural enrichment, leadership opportunities and peer bonding. Students can participate in creative dance, step dance, cheerleading, choir, drum line and various sports teams. These activities provide opportunities that students may not otherwise receive.

name: University Center for the Performing Arts - Arts Alive After School Program
introduction: Arts Alive is a new, state of the art professional performing arts program offering quality training in an after school setting with pickup from many of our local schools. This program is backed by professionals with extensive knowledge in the performing arts in a facility that has been serving the arts community in Broward County for 35 years. Your child will be supervised by an experienced adult at all times. Not only will they receive the high-est standard of performing arts education but they will receive instruction in a quality environment. Activities in the performing arts enhance children’s confidence, self-esteem and academic abilities.
additionalInfo: Dance; Acting; Voice; Arts and Crafts; Healthy after-school snack; Performance opportunities in our 100-seat theater; Specialty classes in acro/tumbling, musical theater, homework study

name: Summit Kids Academy - Kids’ Square
introduction: At Summit Kids Academy, our commitment to kids extends beyond age 5, when children move on from our Pre-K program to kindergarten and beyond. We are pleased to provide after school care for children ages 5-12. “Kids’ Square,” our after school program, provides a personalized, safe, fun place for older kids to stay after the school day ends. In keeping with our philosophy that kids learn through play and by following their own interests, our after school program offers plenty of opportunities for creativity and movement. Here, students can do their homework, play sports, enjoy our iPad lab, develop their own creative projects, and are given time to socialize with other kids in a warm and friendly environment. This is after-school care that’s both secure and fun!

name: Surf Training After School Program
introduction: Lucas Morley’s After School Surf Training program in Port Saint Lucie Florida not only teaches children self-confident, self-discipline, and how to be successful in life. Most parents do and try to do everything to teach their children every second they have them, but many Surf Training After School Program parents need some assistance for 2-4 hours during the day. These 2-4 hours are some of the most import hours in a child’s life. Lucas Morley’s Surf Training After School Program in Florida is a place where the children will connect with other children the same age and learn from older kids in St. Lucie County, Florida. Our Surf Training After School program motivates kids to be the best that they can be in and out of the water so one day they can make valuable contributions to their society.

name: American Top Team Aventura After School @ Ojus Elementary School
introduction: America Top Team Aventura proudly offers After School programs for Ojus Elementary School. If your children is between the ages of 5 and 12 years old, he or she may enroll into our Martial Arts After School enrichment program, and learn self defense to prevent Bullying. We provide transportation as part of our program for Students of Ojus Elementary School. At American Top Team Aventura, the well being of your child is very important, so we also provide Snacks, or your child can bring his/her favorite snack. Our After School Program for Students of Ojus Elementary School is all-inclusive. There is no extra charge to attend on early release days or school employee planning days.

name: Orlando Gymnastics After School Program
introduction: We offer a variety of classes including preschool gymnastics, recreational gymnastics classes for boys and girls, tumbling classes, cheerleading, after school, summer and holiday camps, birthday parties, and open gym nights for kids and adults. We have all competitive levels of boys and girls gymnastics, with expert coaches from around the world. Orlando Gymnastics also offers teen and adult group fitness with Bootcamp, Pilates, Zumba, and more in our private dance studio. At Orlando Gymnastics, we foster physical and emotional well-being through positive coaching and fun, active classes for kids of all ages and ability levels.
additionalInfo: 1 Hour Gymnastics Class Daily; Cooperative Games; Homework Time (with assistance from our instructors); Daily Snack & Drink Provided; Supervised Free Play

name: Frontline For Kids Inc.
introduction: Frontline for Kids is an intervention and prevention after school program established in 2000 by Mr. Jerome Zohndyuwayee Gayman. This visionary believed there was a better, more preventive way to ensure the personal success of our youth. His goals for the program include providing on-going leadership, direction and long term support to students during their most difficult years of development.
additionalInfo: Art; Orchestra; Piano; Flute; Guitar; Reading; Math; Homework Assistance; Recreation; Snack & Hot Meal

name: Anclote Elementary - PLACE Program
introduction: Pasco Learning and Activity Centers of Enrichment (PLACE) is a school-age before and after school activity program operated by the District School Board of Pasco County. PLACE is designed to provide an active and enriching environment for children who must arrive at school early, stay late and/or require supervised activities on most school holidays. Participation is limited to elementary school children, in kindergarten through grade five. The school cafeteria and outside play areas are utilized for PLACE activities. Supervision is provided by school board staff at a ratio of one adult to 25 children. The number of children enrolled at each site is determined by the spacial limitations and number of staff employed.
additionalInfo: Homework and Reading; Science, Technology, Engineering, Math; Recreational Activities and Cooperative Games; Cultural Enrichment Experiences; Special Interest Clubs; Creative Expression through Music, Drama, Dance, Art; Crafts
pricing: Weekly Tuition: 1st Child $49.00, 2nd Child $45.00, Additional: $35.00; Before School Only: 35.00; After School Only: $35.00; Summer Tuition: $64.00; Before/After Drop In: 29.00, Full Day Drop In: $49.00; Registration Fee (Non‐refundable): $25.00; Late Payment Fee: $10.00; Late Pick Up Fee: 15.00 per child for every 15 minutes or any portion thereof

name: Kickin' Kids After School Martial Arts Program
introduction: This school year, enroll your child in our Kickin' Kids After School Martial Arts Program, and see how our martial arts programs for kids can teach so much more than just punching and kicking. Our after school program will teach your child: Respect, Self-Control, Self-Discipline,  Focus/Concentration, Self-Protection, Problem Solving, Goal Setting... and MORE!!! Our after school programs are perfect for children of DeLand, DeBary, Deltona, and Orange City. We are not a licensed child care facility. Instead, we are a licensed martial arts school providing a constructive alternative to traditional daycare. Each afternoon program is planned with a variety of structured group activities such as karate and tumbling classes, life and safety skill lessons, fitness and flexibility training as well as organized fun time to encourage healthy socialization skills. And best yet, it's convenient and affordable since it combines after school care with karate training for less than the price of both, and you don't have to rush from work to get your kids to classes.
